<quote>I pickpocket with my rogue, I don't see anything wrong with it. After all, rogue is a nice word for thief, which is what they are.</quote><br>
First off a rogue in EQ is not a thief.  He is a damage dealer who can be sneaky when necessary.  Second Rogue means:<br>
<br>
<bold>rogue (rg)<br>
n. <br>
An unprincipled, deceitful, and unreliable person; a scoundrel or rascal. <br>
One who is playfully mischievous; a scamp. <br>
A wandering beggar; a vagrant. <br>
A vicious and solitary animal, especially an elephant that has separated itself from its herd. <br>
An organism, especially a plant, that shows an undesirable variation from a standard </bold><br>
<br>
You will notice that while rogue can mean deceitful, it does not mean thief.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<quote>They are shady, they are clever, they are swift. Stealing is what "rogues" do best, and I'll be damned if I don't put it to good use.</quote><br>
Hmmmm see point number 1.  Damage is what rogues do best.  Second best would be corpse retrieval, and third is scoutting out areas, maybe sneak pulling.  Stealing is maybe 5th maybe.  Of course maybe what you mean here is YOUR rogue is best at stealing from his group.  Oh wait you can solo your rogue(possibly the worst class in EQ for soloing) so that must not be it.<br>
<br>
 <quote>I think its sad how people complain about "rogues" pick pocketing. Alot of it is out of jealousy, the rest is conscience. If you don't like it, play a rogue, or just don't group with them. For all you rogues out there I encourage pick pocketing. Not only for roleplaying purposes, but to play the rogue class as it was truly meant to be. Every class has it's special skills, spells, or abilities that help then earn a little cash. This is your's, use it.<br>
<br>
P.S. What they don't know can't hurt em.</quote><br>
This is just so much bullshit.  It has to do with a member of a group taking something from the group without sharing.  Kinda like ninja looting before the loot messages were added.  Or was that just jealousy too??<br>
<br>
And actually what they don't know can and does hurt the rogue class.  See when people like you come along and talk about how pickpockets is the defining ability of a rogue and how all rogues should do it whenever they want, it gives all the people who may not know about rogues a bad taste about them.  Then you see it is those of us who play rogues as main characters who are hurt.  Sure if you can't find somewhere to solo your rogue you can always go back and play your mana sink.  But I and many others like me have worked at getting up to a decent level and when I have to put up with not getting invited to a group because they are afraid I will steal all the loot it is very frustrating.<br>
