Think about it people. A rogue is a great addition to a group.  The extra damage output a rogue provides far outweighs his/her occassional use of pick pocket skill.  The paranoia about a rogue stealing from a group is really unfounded and IMO simply uncalled for.<br>
<br>
 <p><b>Greywolffe Silverstarr</b><br>
54th Vicar of Tunare</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umismort.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mismort</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/26/01 12:34:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pick pocket</span><hr size=1> Master loot group, no picking unless it is a group of friends, or you are masterlooting. (If you ask a rogue to masterloot, you are trusting the rogue more then other classes, since he/she can pick gems spells etc and you wont see them)<br>
<br>
Free for all loot, ask group before hand, if you can pick some mobs.  If group says yes, be fair about it.  Pick what you would normally get looting.<br>
<br>
Group as a whole are assholes to you?  Up to you, but as a rogue you can fuck over the loot table pretty bad in places like OS.<br>
<br>
Pre 50 pickpocket is pretty harmless.  Post 50 you can really hurt groups (or raids...poh etc) when you pick.  In OS as long as the mobs take to die, you would have 6 or 7 chances to pick the mob.  Gems, spells have a tendancy to pick out first, then coin starting from plat down to copper.  <br>
<br>
There is a potential for abuse there. I think this is where it comes down to your reputation.  If you group with a rogue and notice cash loot is a little low for plat and gem loot is almost non-existant...maybe you should pay attention.  Group with the rogue on a regular basis and notice loot is FUBAR everytime you group then it may be prudent to talk about it.<br>
<br>
The only problem is that loot is variable, and it is almost impossible to prove a rogue is picking, unless every loot is 1 plat 1 gold 1 silver 1 copper.<br>
<br>
Solution: For Verent to give all mobs a chance to emote or shout the little thief thing.  Right now its only human mob types.<br>
<br>
Also remember that we cant pick &quot;animals&quot; or &quot;undead&quot;...at least as far as I know.<br>
<br>
LIttle off-topic rant:<br>
Oh yeah, when a rogue, or any class for that matter, is doing a cr we usually dont ask for a donation, but remember without that cr its gonna take alot longer to get that res, and we are risking our xp to get your corpses.  Little more risk then that cleric that is sitting in the zone saying no res for joo unless joo got 100 plat.....<br>
<br>
Remember to THANK people who drag your corpses, that is all most of us ask<br>
<br>
