<font face="Arial" size=2><I>When people ask me why one would want to be a rake, I tell them I get to lie in a shed with a hoe all day.</I></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utyrasdjunoesque.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tyras DJunoesque</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/27/01 8:12:11 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=www.jacksonville.net/~madmoose/photo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pick pocket</span><hr size=1> Hi, my name is Tyras and I am a pickpocket. <br>
<br>
There are times when picking a mob is innappropriate.  Like when there is a designated master looter who splits coin with the group. <br>
For the most part though, I pickpocket mobs when there is a loot-whore in the group or it's free for all and I pick but don't loot.  <br>
Any time I pick gems or spells I always put them up for random or in guild raid scenarios, give them to the designated spell/gem mule. <br>
There is no reason someone should be upset at a pp'ing rogue who splits with the group and randoms the gems/spells.  Any show of anger towards an upfront pp'er is just jealousy. <br>
The real valueable items can't be picked anyway. (lore, no drop) items. <br>
If you suspect the rogue in your group is pp'ing and not splitting then just make sure they arent looting dead mobs also.  Pretty fair to do one and not the other. <br>
Tyras D`Junoesque &lt;Magister&gt;<br>
